<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1436,586,1115]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,934,960]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</emphasis>
Kato’s description of 
<taxonomicName box="[578,741,935,960]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Petalocephaloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticapitata">
<emphasis box="[578,741,935,960]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">P. laticapitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is of a female. He made no examination of genitalia and no reference to leg or tarsal characters that might distinguish 
<taxonomicName box="[857,1024,973,998]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Petalocephaloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticapitata">
<emphasis box="[857,1024,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">P. laticapitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other closely related ledrine genera. It is possible that this species is a junior synonym of one in another genus, perhaps for which only a male has been described. The location of the 
<typeStatus box="[688,738,1050,1076]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[899,1063,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Petalocephaloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticapitata">
<emphasis box="[899,1063,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">P. laticapitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, part of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kato, M." box="[1165,1329,1050,1076]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="431 - 440" refId="ref57432" refString="Kato, M. (1931) Japanese Ledridae. Dobutsugaku Zasshi, 43, 431 - 440." type="journal article" year="1931">Kato’s (1931)</bibRefCitation>
personal collection, is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
